<script>
    function luc21893_refresh_cell(cell) {
        if( cell.luc21893 ) return;
        cell.luc21893 = true;
        console.debug('New code cell found...' );
        
        var div = document.createElement('DIV');            
        cell.parentNode.insertBefore( div, cell.nextSibling );
        div.style.textAlign = 'right';
        var a = document.createElement('A');
        div.appendChild(a);
        a.href='#'
        a.luc21893 = cell;
        a.setAttribute( 'onclick', "luc21893_toggle(this); return false;" );

        cell.style.visibility='hidden';
        cell.style.position='absolute';
        a.innerHTML = '[show code]';        
                
    }
    function luc21893_refresh() {                
        if( document.querySelector('.code_cell .input') == null ) {            
            // it apeears that I am in a exported html
            // hide this code
            var codeCells = document.querySelectorAll('.jp-InputArea')
            codeCells[0].style.visibility = 'hidden';
            codeCells[0].style.position = 'absolute';                        
            for( var i = 1; i < codeCells.length; i++ ) {
                luc21893_refresh_cell(codeCells[i].parentNode)
            }
            window.onload = luc21893_refresh;
        }                 
        else {
            // it apperas that I am in a jupyter editor
            var codeCells = document.querySelectorAll('.code_cell .input')
            for( var i = 0; i < codeCells.length; i++ ) {
                luc21893_refresh_cell(codeCells[i])
            }            
            window.setTimeout( luc21893_refresh, 1000 )
        }        
    }
    
    function luc21893_toggle(a) {
        if( a.luc21893.style.visibility=='hidden' ) {
            a.luc21893.style.visibility='visible';        
            a.luc21893.style.position='';
            a.innerHTML = '[hide code]';
        }
        else {
            a.luc21893.style.visibility='hidden';        
            a.luc21893.style.position='absolute';
            a.innerHTML = '[show code]';
        }
    }
    
    luc21893_refresh()
</script>

def AlertFromBinar(AlertNum):
    a = bin(int(AlertNum))
    x = []
    for i in range (len(a)):
        if a[i] == '1':
            x.append(i+1)
    return x


def AlertFromHex(AlertNum):
    HexMold = '0x0000'
    x = []
    ind = 0
    for i in AlertNum:
        if ind > 1:
            if i != '0':
                x.append(HexMold[:ind] + i + HexMold[ind+1:])
        ind = ind + 1
    return x
                
            

def GiveAlerts (df):
    FoundError = False
    for num in range(1,7): 
        i = 2 # skip on two first row
        count = 0
        temp_i = 0
        temp_val = '0x0000 '
        for val in data[' EngineDiagStatus' + str(num)]:
            if (val != '0x0000 ') & (val != temp_val):    # Find the error
                for item in AlertFromHex(val):  #Run on every bit in the decimal/hex value of the error
                    if (i != temp_i + 1):   # Chacks if the error happens on follow measurments and how many times
                        if (item != '0x0000 '): # The zeros values 0x0000 comes with space char at the end of the string
                            print ('The Alert description is: ', AlertsTable['EngineDiagStatus' + str(num)][item] + '.', 'It happend on index: ', i)
                            FoundError = True
                
                temp_i = i
        
            elif (val != '0x0000 ') & (val == temp_val):
                count = count + 1
            elif (val != temp_val) & (count != 0):
                print ('This Alert happend ' + str(count) + ' times in row')
        
            i = i + 1
            temp_val = val
    
    if (FoundError == False):
        print ('No Errors found in this file.')
